content.detailedDescription: I reported the same type lights last night. tonight they seemed to be the same but on a different direction.  still sort of sw to ne.  the lead object had a light connected to it---a nike shaped swoosh. the beam came off from the object and curved back around.  the following object was farther behind than last night by half of the span of the sky.  i took my flashlight and blinked it at the object, and within seconds the lead object was no where to be found as well as the following.
content.summary: Bright star-like image with nike swoosh like light connected following behind was another star like object

content.detailedDescription: At 7:45 pm i stepped out to retrieve the mail when i saw two star like objects directly above me heading in a northeastern direction. the lead object resembled a low orbit satellite in brightness/size, but the second object was big/bright and seemed to follow the smaller lead objects course exactly, single file. if these objects were at the same altitude as a low orbit satellite then the second object had to be very large, as it seemed to be 2 to 3 times the size of the biggest star in the sky. these objects were moving slowly and took approximately 2 to 3 minutes before they were out of sight, and no sound of jet engines or anything could be heard throughout the entire event. i live in the fresno area, very close to the sierra's.
content.summary: Two star like object coming from the s.W. bearing n.E.

content.detailedDescription: We where coming into the dock area from fishing, it had just got dark. i was watching a satellite glide across the night sky when i noticed a bright, star like object floating across the sky. it wasn't flashing, it was solid white. then another one followed behind it. you could tell that they where pretty high, but still the brightest  thing in the sky by far. we watched them for 4 or 5 minuets, we where all so mesmerized by it, we hit a group of small rocks, sticking out of the water. then, one by one, they faded away.
content.summary: Two star like objects floating across the sky

content.detailedDescription: My girlfriend was coming home from work and she was driving west and from telegraph on 696 freeway. she saw an object hovering in the distance which looked like a disc in shape, but she could only see the dark outline and then she saw as she got closer she saw a red and green light on one side and the other side had a white light on it, from the angle she was at. it was not moving but just hovering at about the height of a cell phone antenna and as she traveled under orchard lake rd overpass she looked away for a split second and it was gone. she knows it wasnt a plane because none of the lights were blinking or flashing and the size was about 50ft in diameter. she looked for it in the daylight and she said nothing could of been that high hovering and looking the way it did.
content.summary: Hovering object

content.detailedDescription: At 9:22 pm i was watching the sky and saw 2 star like objects moving sw to ne.  these objects were not blinking or changing color.  they were solid white with no noise.  we live in the country and have no light or sound pollution.  i watched these objects for about 2 and half minutes till they went past a hill.
content.summary: Two star like objects sw to ne

content.detailedDescription: i was sitting outside on my computer faceing south. between 8:30 p.M. and 9:00 p.M. two lights caught my eye.  they were headed north going pretty fast but not crazy fast. they was not flashing at all & had the same brightness also size. they kept the same distance from each other about 3 or 4 hundred yards one directly behind the other.
content.summary: 2 lights following each other

content.detailedDescription:
I was in front of my house - standing on the driveway. i had gone out to see my daughter and her friend drive away to a friend's party.

as i was walking back to my front door - i noticed a bright orange light just east of my house. at first i thought it was an airplane, but the lights were much different from the many airplane lights that i have seen. the lights seemed to get bigger and the orange color brighter after just watching it for about 5 - 10 seconds.

the light was a glowing bright orange ball and slowly moving over my neighbors��� houses about 500 feet on the sky. light was moving west bound and then slowly moved south bound towards 145th street. light did not make a sound and it did not have blinking lights as you would see on an airplane.

after about 10 - 15 seconds of watching the light in awe, i ran to the front door and called for my wife to come out and see. my wife came out and saw the light as it slowly moved south bound towards lockport and disappearing in the horizon.


i then called 911 to report it at about 10:40 p.M. i asked the answering office if there were any other calls reporting the light over the sky and i was told that there had been one other call making the same report.

i am not claiming that i saw a ufo ��� but it sure was not an airplane. i would really like to know what i saw.
content.summary: Glowing orange light and slowly moving south

content.detailedDescription: My brother was in the backyard having a beer with a neighbor, he called me and said run outside you have to see this, ran out and looked up and saw two bright lights. objects were similar to stars following each other perfectly perpendicular, one behind the other. objects were travelling at high speeds, (almost as fast as a shooting star), but perfectly straight. i could not believe my eyes, i have seen many shooting stars, satellites, weather ballons, fast jets, rockets, etc.  this was completely deferent in movement, and speed. there were travelling from wsw to ene.  i saw the light/star like objects turn red/orange and vanished what looked to be in an up motion.
content.summary: Two bright lights following each other, perfectly parallel, turned red/orange and dissapeared, movement west south west to east north east

content.detailedDescription: Bight white light like a star giong throught the trees but not zigzag it went stright and then blink it was gone.Within just a matter of a few secs it was behind where it disapred over the mountain.
content.summary: Flying throught trees

content.detailedDescription: While setting in the living room of my apartment watching t.V., i heard what sounded like someone outside talking loudly, so i steped out on the balcony to see who it was. there was nobody outside, but i concluded that it must have been the downstairs neighbors. it was a cool but comfortable evening, so i decided to stand outside for a few minutes. the sky was mainly clear with some clouds low in the eastern sky, but the stars were easily observed. having a background in artillery survey and land navigation in the military, its normal for me to look for survey/navigational stars and constellations in the sky. as i looked up at the big dipper(ursa major) i noticed two star like objects traveling about three finger widths apart at arms distance moving from west to east on a steady course and maintaining a constant interval passing just below the north star(polaris). the two objects were of about the same brightness(magnitude) as the pointer stars in the big dipper. they did not blink or sway as they moved through the sky. i called out to my girlfriend who was working on her computer in the living room to come as a witness and to get her perspective. we observed as they continued on a steady course until they faded away. they did not go beyond the horizon, but looked as though they were climbing out of the atmosphere. i noted the time and date on my wrist watch as 9:18pm 09-08-2009. the observation lasted approximatly two minutes from beginning to end.
content.summary: Two star like objects moving from w. to e. in northern sky over pittsburgh

content.detailedDescription: Where is located this hunted woods?
content.summary: Where is located this hunted woods?

content.detailedDescription:
Was disturbed from sleep at 4am by a feeling of urgency to be outside. made my coffee and proceded outside with the dogs. sitting on the trunk of the car and viewing the sky, upon first sight nothing seen. then, coming in fast from southwest approximately 3 to 4 miles out (from haunted woods), appears to be a saucer like craft heading east - southeast. stopping and hovering approximately 3 to 4 miles from my location, 2 beams of light radiating from what then became a star-like object (because of distance) with rotating colors of red, blue, yellow, green and brilliant white. object was moving eradically in all directions but, staying in close proximaty to (ocala national forest) bombing range. hound dogs in the neighborhood started whining and howling and barking, while my dogs ran about in all directions and whined alot. the horses in the field next door were acting strangely also. there were no sounds of insects or birds except, that of an owl hooting.
my reactions are as they always are and have been for many years, saying to myself, it's about time. it seems that throughout my life they come every 3 years. i'm an old veteran at this. since i was 3-years-old, up to now and i'm sure years to come. i have worked with m.U.F.O.N. before and have been requested to go on investigations of other reports in my area because, i am tuned in to whatever they are. i have in the past worked with alien abductees, was for awhile a crop-circle interpretor and have come in contact with the men-in-black. i was an advisor on ufo landing sites in various areas across the nation and have given lectures on the subject.
i lost sight of the object by coming back inside to report the info to you. i thought since it had been 3 years since my last sighting that you would be most interested hearing from me again.

note: haunted woods, a place where a lot of very strange activities happen. two unpaved roads run through it from east to west and drivers have reported to the local sherrifs department, sightings during day light and after dark of phantoms, ghost, aliens, strange crafts flying at tree top levels, creatures, cryptids, brilliant orbs floating along sides of road and sometimes seen crossing, voices, screams, sounds of running and people going missing. this is where my last encounter was. i was traveling west with some friends, a saucer craft followed along the north side of the car a little over a hundred feet away, when i stopped it stopped, when i proceded it proceded, when i went faster it went faster. but, when i reached the edge of the woods, it vanished. all in the car witnessed the sighting.
local sherrifs department tries to deter people from stopping or wondering in these woods. this is a continous ongoing event.
content.summary: Moving eradically with beam of light and aray of colors, e-se, 3-4 miles

content.detailedDescription: I was watering some plants around 7:45 pm i looked over my shoulder to see a light in the sky moving...It did not look like a plane but what really got my attention was the smaller object travelling somewhat in front of it...It was a smaller starlike object. they were fairly low and made no noise. they did not warble but were in perfect alignment and moved with ease and purpose very slowly until out of sight. here is a spliced together video clip made from 3 short videos i was able to get...Sorry about the quality my camera will not let me focus or view through the eyepiece when in record mode and it gives me a lot of trouble with less than stellar results. i'd like to say i see a lot of weird things in the sky around here. i don't know what these are but thought it was odd enough to report.
content.summary: 2 slowly moving starlike objects. 1 larger than the other and following the other.

content.detailedDescription: Observed two star-like objects flying overhead in normal speed toward ne direction of brea and yorba linda at 7:48pm and quickly took out digital camera nikon p60 coolpix and video recorded for a short duration of  1'38" until it faded away. no flashing lights had been seen and the first one is brighter than the following one behind. silence and no other engine noises could be heard. both husband and wife witnessed.
content.summary: Observed two star-like objects passing overhead in unisom speed over anaheim

content.detailedDescription: First i must say, i never did believe in u.F.O s coming from a christian family,we were taught there was not such a thing. that god created man and the universe,which i know he did. but on that night it change my thinking, that in this vast universe god could have made other beings. well back to the sighting.I have not share this experience with much people,because the thing, they think your crazy.Well to the sighting. my nephew and i were siting on buckets,fishing off the boat ramp in port deposit md, at the park at the end of town. siting there for about a hour,my nephew ask me, uncle rodney what are those lights at the other side of the river. the river is about a mile wide. so i said to him, it's probably a helicopter. and being at night,the thought hit me,you can hear voices across the river. then no soon i thought that,i hear like this humming noice. i look to my right, and about 50 feet up along the bank ling we see this u.F.O. hoveing. then it came very slowley coming toward us,and when it got right above our heads, it stay there hoveing for a minute or so.Then i said to my nephew,do you see what i see? he couldn't say nothing.You coudn't feel nothing,and it didn't,it didn't do anything to the water.So i just stood there looking up and in,all what this u.F.O. look like. first i notice it was shape like a f-117 night hawk. but the metal wasn't smooth. it look like something you would see in starwars. in the milltary they have a helicopter called the apache,which has a longbow on top. this u.F.O. had something like thaton top,but it was lit up,with different colors.And it had two big lights,under,say the wings like,which were about a foot in diameter.Which were very bright.Then it just slowley went down the bank a little further,and you could hear like it kit in gear in went toward the middle of the river,and went up and shot over route 95 bridge.I wish we would have had a camera or something, because just 50 feet over our heads,we would had some interesting pictures.When i see our lord, that's one of the questions i will be asking him.
content.summary: It was shape like the millary plane f-117  night hawk, and also on top  it had a lit pan cake shape.

content.detailedDescription:
Storm, cumulus clouds were gathering over me.  as i happened to look up, i noticed a green, undulating shape, which was causing the clouds to appear to be breathing.  as it moved, so did the clouds.  it moved from a storm cloud, which had had some lighting activity, over to another cloud.  then it moved to some cirus cloud, which were more transparent, allowing it's shape to become more discernable.  it then began to move around  behind many of the clouds and before i knew it, it was out in the open.  the green activity, which look remarkably like that of a tesla coil, was enclosed in a clear, circular object, which appeared to be, at least, one mile in diameter.  remaining at a high altitude, it moved directly over me.  i felt that it knew that i was following it's movements.  it then moved slowly over to another set of cirus clouds, and then it completely zoomed out of sight.  i had a distinct feeling that it knew that i could see it, especially when it moved directly over me and then into the small cirus cloud.

i saw the object several more times throughout the day as the electrical storm continued.  the lighting was spectacular and the object seemed to be drawn to the energy being put out by the lighting producing clouds.

the outter membrane of this object remained clear, at all times.  the internal tesla looking activity, was emerald green in color, looking remarkably like a flat, clear tesla coil.
content.summary: Green undulating object inside clear circle.

content.detailedDescription: I observed another star like object on the evening of september 8th. the second of two sightings this evening. this also was a star like object but this time in the western sky and at about the same height as jupiter again. this was a single object that moved slowly to the north and then faded quickly. two in one night is pretty spectacular for the boise area.
content.summary: Star like object in the western sky

content.detailedDescription: Driving home from south boise to east boise i observed a bright star where none should be. i realized it was moving when i stopped my car. i then noticed a dimmer object beside it moving at the same speed. the objects were at the same height in the sky as jupiter and to the east. they moved slowly together in the same direction for about one minute before quickly fading away. they stayed the same distance from each other the entire time. there were no blinking lights or noise and appeared to be very high in the sky. very exciting to watch, whatever they were.
content.summary: Two star like objects moving together at the same speed

content.detailedDescription: So, there i was walking down a dark path outside of my apartment complex. i do this often. i happened to look up at the sky (as i do seemingly do wndlessly nowadays) and spot a bright white orb coming from the south. this is no surprise to me, for i have seen them often, yet i still become excited. it's coming from the far south, traveling at a steady speed to the north. as it gets closer, i watch it wobble a bit. i decided to sit down on the path and watch it hover over my head, but soon realize that it it slowing down. it's traveling at such a slow speed, that it's difficult to detect any movement at all. it then speeds up again, travels about an inch (from my perspective), stops again, repeats, then moves about an inch to the left. this is when it suddenly hit me. i thought, "wait a minute, where is jupider?" i had seen jupider every night-gazing at it's bright presence. this is where it is extremely difficult to explain. i realized that the entire time that i was watching this orb move from the south, that it was the only light in the sky. when it stopped, it stopped exactly where jupider has been every night. there was no jupider present at the time of the sighting. as far as my mind in concerned, the orb stopped right where jupider should have been. i can look out of my window right now and see jupider in it's normal spot. my head was tinkered with at that moment what happened. this isn't my typical orb sighting. i still feel extremely confused right now! ;) part of my brain is saying that jupider, at this time, is indeed itself. the other half is saying that it's still the orb that stopped there 30 minutes ago. i have been getting frequent "brain buzzes" ever since.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Watching orb coming from south - headed north. it slows down to a stop, moves a little more, and seems to turn  into jupider.

content.detailedDescription: Two star like objects observed to the east of boise at approximately the same height in the sky as jupiter. one object was as bright as jupiter. the other was dimmer. the objects moved together at the same speed slowly and for about 1 minute then both slowly faded away. i thought they were stars at first until i stopped my car. at that point i noticed they were moving. they were not aircraft/planes.I was driving home from south boise to east boise. i first noticed them when i looked up and saw a bright star where none should be. i then saw the dimmer object moving with it. i felt a little nervous at first but then thought it was pretty cool. i lost sight of the objects when they faded away. they both faded at the same time.
content.summary: Two star like objects, one bright , one dim moving together at the same speed. slowly faded away.

content.detailedDescription: Looking south off of my back deck    noticed 2 large white orbs following the same path.  the size of jupiter with a span of the size of a cigarette pack at arms length apart.  traveling out of the south with a path to the n.E.       they were visible for about 1 minute.  the first one faded out first and the second went through its path and seemed to turn east before it also faded.  no blinking lights and no sound.     have seen many "satellites" and some "others".  have never seen a double b4.  moved here from sheboygan in dec. 0-8 and am pleased to see so many unexplainable things.
content.summary: Identical to waukesha sighting

content.detailedDescription: My 23 yr.Old son and i were on our way back from a neighborhood convenience store, and coming south on 137th st.Towards 49th. as we came out of the housing and entered the open area surrounded by fields, at the same time my son and i both said "what is that!" in the sky above us, approx. 1/8th mile distant were 4 bright red lights with an orange-yellow glow in the centers.This was directly south of our position and we were heading towards it. it was configured like a triangle with the 4th light at the center of it.At first when i saw it through the trees, my first thought was that a plane had exploded and was coming down, these lights were so bright in intensity. we slowed way down as did the other traffic. i know there have to be other witnesses, as there was alot of other cars on the road, and 137th is a main  connection to a main thoroughfare.My son told me to speed up and try to get closer. as i did this the triangle began to descend then rise back up. it did this several times as i tried to find a place to pull off. once parked my son jumped out to get a better look, and i watched it and glanced to see if i could exit the truck also. as i got out my son said " it's gone, it just disappeared. i could'nt see it anywhere, so we got back in the truck and drove the 4 blocks back to my home and told my husband and brother-in-law what we had just seen.We were both pretty excited,as we have both witnessed "things" that did'nt seem natural in the sky before. and we were both aware of what we were witnessing.
content.summary: 4 bright reddish lights, changing direction, altitude,as it hovered.Followed by several helicopters searching the area.

content.detailedDescription:

one behind the other, maintaining the same distance from each other, as if being "towed". i called my son outside to look when the "stars" light was not strobing, getting dimmer or changing in any way as they moved away. several planes were in the area with visible strobes, and i could hear the other planes, but these stars were silent from directly overhead to disappearing on the horizon. i believe this is what was seen at fort dodge earlier?

content.detailedDescription:

size of the statue is about 23meters frome the ground.  lens i used to take this picture was samsung 16-45mm for pentax k20d. (pls refer exif data)

content.detailedDescription: She indicated that she has had one previous very dramatic sighting at the age of 18 and occurred in december 1989 or 1990. she also indicated that she is an accomplished medium and partially supports herself by giving readings for individuals in the community. she is acutely aware of the realities outside of the traditional three-dimensional world. her original sighting occurred at the approximate age of 18 when she was driving home late at night on the road between la junta and los animas colorado at approximately 10:00 pm. she noted a great light hovering over an abandoned farmhouse and observed a large line of cars stopped on the side of the road watching the spotlight. she got out of her car to watch along with the other observers and  watched this  spotlight moving toward them silently. it abruptly shut off its spotlight and she was able to observe multicolored lights around its large oblong dimension of approximatly 40 yards. she remembers remarking to the truck driver standing near her that she had a camera in the car and was going to get it out. at that point there is a blank episode and she came to an unknown time later with the unknown object approximately a half a mile away and moving off into the distance. she had no way of explaining why she did not get her camera out of the car. she has no recollections of any other events happening to her in the blank interval. she drove onto the next town and stopped at a pay telephone to call her mother and report the incident. she remembers she was crying while talking to her mother. she reported no health problems during or after the incident. she gave me the name of her mother and her phone number so that i would be able to call her mother and get more details.
content.summary: Bright search light hovering over an abandoned farmhouse.

content.detailedDescription: I was outside working on my truck between 8:30pm and 9:00pm. i got a weird  feeling and needed to look up. when i did i was in awe. a very bright point of light brighter than jupiter was directly over head. to the right and in front of the light was a smaller point of light. both objects were moving northeast and had no flashing strobes or any red or green lights. i ran inside to get my wife and grabbed my binoculars, simmons model 1107 10x50. i looked through the binoculars at the brighter object. it still had the same shape but a little hint of red was evident. the smaller object was starting to fade out. within a minute the smaller light vanished. the large and still bright object was gradually dimming but could still be seen very clearly with the naked eye. an airliner was approaching the large light from the southwest. as the airliner got closer, the light would fade even more. eventually the light vanished. the airliner stayed on its course. my wife and i watched the area for about 2 minutes. then directly above us another light appeared out of nowhere. it was just as bright as jupiter. it sat still for about 2 seconds and then started moving north slowly. i watched through my binoculars for maybe 10 seconds until it faded out. it appeared to fade out not from moving north but from moving up away from earth. i sat outside for one hour and saw many jets but no other bright lights.
content.summary: Very bright star-like point of light with smaller light next to it moving northeast

content.detailedDescription: Labor day evening. i had just pulled into my boyfriends driveway. it was around 9pm to 9:30pm. i got out of the car and glanced to the south-ish direction at scorpius. i am a scorpio so i tend to look, and anteres seemed weird. very bright and white, anteres is always red. i found it weird and went inside the basement area to see my boyfriend. he was not there. a minute or so later i stepped back out into the driveway to make a call on my cellphone when i saw the star that should have been anteres star moving in an upward and easterly direction. i about fell down. it only lasted a few seconds. the star is still present. on the 8th at around 3 am i saw the star sitting still in the sky. but it was not were it should have been. it was sitting back in the place anteres had been. i don't know if it is a satellite but it's very bright. bright like the space station is bright.
content.summary: Like a fake star

content.detailedDescription: I live in elizabeth colorado i happened to look up at the sky, this is about 8:45pm mountain. noticed two very bright objects traveling at a high rate of speed in unison or formation going from a southwest to a northeast direction. there were no faa required lighting such as a strobe light or nav. lights and there was no sound. they appeared to have a slight turn or curve pattern. we eventually lost sight because the lights went behind our rather large threes on our lot.I was so amazed i had my wife look at this as well. we have no explaination for what we saw.
content.summary: Noticed 2 very bright objects moving southwest to northeast atahigh rate of speed had a slight curvature of flight pattern.

content.detailedDescription: Was come back from a friends house and was watching the coburg hill me and my family watched a campfire just appear out of nowhere and then it move about 20 feet and just stop.Then something shot out from the right side and just took off.That was it for about 20 mins and then this rainbow light just appears to the left of the campfire light and it slowly heads over to it kind of at a angle.And then the light is gone within a matter of a few seconds poof gone.Light the light was still there when we got home so i called the police and reported what i had seen.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Looks like a campfire burning in the middle of the trees
